EP  - 542
VL  - 24
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A field experiment was conducted to investigate effects of removal of a performance-contingent reward on subordinates? perceptions of their supervisors? sources of influence. A significant increase was found in perceptions of supervisors? use of punishment, but reward, referent, and organizationally-sanctioned power declined significantly. Expert power was unaffected by removal of the incentive system.
AB  - A field experiment was conducted to investigate effects of removal of a performance-contingent reward on subordinates? perceptions of their supervisors? sources of influence. A significant increase was found in perceptions of supervisors? use of punishment, but reward, referent, and organizationally-sanctioned power declined significantly. Expert power was unaffected by removal of the incentive system.
